physical_examinations.relevant_findings: Normal neurological examination except for poor recall (only one of three objects after three minutes) and mild temporal disorientation (unable to tell the day of the week).
Patient was lethargic post-surgery, showed disorientation for time, and had retrograde and anterograde amnesia.
physical_examinations.changes_over_time: After surgery, patient gradually showed an increase in affect, cried easily but appropriately, and continued to complain of forgetfulness; three months post-surgery, she was considered recovered.
